   1) Go to www.UICCareers.com  2) Click on “Employer.”  3) Click on “Sign Up and Post Job” on the right-hand side of the screen.  4) Follow the prompts as directed.  5) Within 1-3 business days, you should receive an email confirmation of your registration and job posting.    The UICcareers.com website is accessible to all current students as well as alumni.       UIC Careers Website          Registering for an account on the UICcareers.com website also provides you access to:   Our calendar of events , where you can view upcoming job fairs and recruiting opportunities.  Resume books* (provided upon request), where you can view student resumes based on the criteria (major, graduation date, work authorization, etc.) that you choose.   *Resume books are only provided to external employers, not for on-campus departments or units.  For more information on how to post a new position and check incoming applications , use the button below.       New Position and Incoming Application Details          Employers    Back to main content           Post A Position    UICcareers    Career Fair Information for Employers    On-Campus Interviews    Information Tables & Sessions    Employer Partner Program    Additional Outreach & Student Engagement Opportunities    Directions / Hotels                  UIC Logo        Career Services         Students    Career Planning Guide    Make an Appointment    FAQs      Employers    Post a Position    UICcareers.com      Campus Partners    Campus Partners    Program/Workshop Request Forms        Footer Menu    Career Programs and Events    UICcareers    UIC Student Employment Office         Contact   Suite 3050 1200 West Harrison Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-2300  Fax: (312) 413-0383  careerservices@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    YouTube             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  